<div class="lightblock">
== <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em white;border-bottom: 3px groove var(--theme-border-color);">I. Depiction</span> ==
<center><Div class="image">[[File:Level 994 rw.png|center|250px|link=]]
</div></center>
{{Underline|d8a85c}}
[[Level 994]], also nicknamed as <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em #ffffff88;font-family: 'Chelsea Market';">'''Wacky Place'''</span>, is the 995<sup>th</sup> [[Level List|level]] of the [[Backrooms Wiki|Backrooms]].

The level is an endless, and giggling labyrinth of colourful wacky rooms, each subtly glowing beneath shy, and flickering lights that never seem quite awake. Every room seems like it was arranged by a child with a fondness for mischief; chairs standing atop ceilings, tables disappointedly facing corners, toy chests humming to themselves.

Some rooms have peculiar devices rarely seen twice: switches which politely invite one to adjust gravity, geometry changers that fold the room like origami, and trampolines so enthusiastically bouncy they launch jumpers to the concrete ceiling. Rarely, already [[Object List|documented objects]] can be found as well. Most common ones include, but not limited to: [[Object 20|Cloth Phones]] sitting on wavy tables, [[Object 10|Backshrooms]] in small little pots, [[Object 25|Flashies]] lying on the floor, [[Object 3|Magic Door Knobs]] standing beside a wall waiting to be used, etc.

Majority of these rooms are shaped by the curious hand of [[Phenomenon 14|non-Euclidean geometry]], where corridors curl into spirals and loop back on themselves. Staircases seem like they are going up but secretly lead you down, and walls overlap in soft, but glitchy embraces. Directions become suggestions than rules, and every turn seems like the level itself is leading back; delighted by your confusion.

{{Underline|d8a85c}}
<div class="lightblock">
=== <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em white;border-bottom: 3px groove var(--theme-border-color);">I.I. Oddities</span> ===
<tabber>
|-|Mean Scribbles=
While travelling through [[Level 994]], one may notice rude, and cheeky little sentences on the walls and ceilings. They do not introduce themselves nor apologize; instead, they poke at one's current troubles with exaggeration. Curiously, these mean scribbles seem to especially appear when one looks visibly gloomy or jittery.

|-|Liars' Mirrors=
There are rare, but surprisingly consistent reports of odd mirrors that like to place themselves at the end of hallways or beside staircases. These mirrors are delightful little liars. Instead of sharing a normal reflection, they present an opposite of the individual and the space around them. a nervous individual may find their reflection standing tall, fearless, and similing confidently back through the glass. The hallway behind the reflection may appear gloomier, longer, shorter, and negative in colour.
</tabber>
</div>
{{Underline|d8a85c}}
<div class="lightblock">
=== <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em white;border-bottom: 3px groove var(--theme-border-color);">I.II. Wacky Lunch Place</span> ===
<center><Div class="image">[[File:Level 994 rw2.png|center|250px|link=]]
</div></center>
{{Underline|d8a85c}}
[[Level 994|The Wacky Lunch Place]] is a confusing, and noodle-like jumble of curly hallways that curves around each other like spaghetti. Along the corridors, there are shiny glass rooms, each trying to look exactly like a cafeteria; tables stay miserably, and chairs sit in awkward little clusters. Moreover, dust and mold have claimed the walls and floors; spreading with passion.

The only light comes from widely separated, and shy ceiling lights that seem uninterested in their careers. They glow weakly like if perpetually on the edge of a nap. Most of the time, they lose focus and turn off for a a few seconds; before suddenly waking and blasting a rude, and blinding flash.

This place strongly looks like if a food fight once happened here… and never quite ended. Foods, cups of various drinks, and snacks are scattered across the floors chaotically. At first, some of them appear perfectly edible; sandwiches, fruit, and drinks shining under sleepy lights with a promising look. But a closer look reveals that everything is crafted with plastic.
</div>
{{Underline|d8a85c}}
<div class="lightblock">
=== <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em white;border-bottom: 3px groove var(--theme-border-color);">I.III. Opened Wackiness</span> ===
<center><Div class="image">[[File:Level 994 rw3.png|center|250px|link=]]
</div></center>
{{Underline|d8a85c}}
Climbing one of the level’s awkwardly designed staircases will, on rare times, lead to [[Level 994|the Opened Wackiness]].

From below, the place looks ordinary, like if just another slightly confused section of the level. However, one may notice a rather important architectural mistake: there is no ceiling. The roof appears to have simply left off, which leaves a wide opening above the room.

Looking up through this skylight reveals a misty, and linearly colored sky. Strange celestial shapes and objects move lazily overhead; enormous objects, unfamiliar moons, and other mysterious things that look like they were designed during a very enthusiastic art class.

</div></div>
{{Underline|d8a85c}}
<div class="lightblock">
== <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em white;border-bottom: 3px groove var(--theme-border-color);">III. Entities</span> ==
{{Underline|d8a85c}}
<Div class="lightblock">
=== <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em white;border-bottom: 3px groove var(--theme-border-color);">III.I. Nota Balloon</span> ===

The moment someone steps into the level, they are politely greeted by a single, and cheerfully floating cartoon balloon, also named as [[Level 994|Nota Balloon]]. It flies in the air with enthusiastic steadiness, and the string of it dances like if held by an invisible hand. Less cheerfully, it has a freakishly messed up imitation of the individual’s childhood favorite cartoon character. Its proportions, the smile, and the eyes are on the lowest place of perfection. And without any silly announcement, it begins getting closer like a forgotten close friend.

Nearby, a soft, and whimsical melody plays. It is nostalgic, and comfortable, like a music box half fogged in memory. The music sounds familiar enough to tug at the heart, but still off key. The closer [[Level 994|Nota Balloon]] comes, the clearer the melody becomes.

One must hesitate the feeling that it is innocent. Despite its appearance, the entity is dangerous. With no dramatic attacks, roaring or bullying; reports say that touching it leads to sudden bad consequences. More strangely, the entity always seems aware of the individual’s exact position, even when the individual is hidden.

Although it moves only slightly faster than an average walking speed, it never pauses, and never runs out of enthusiasm. Worse, it can peform the ability to teleport randomly. Rarely, it cuts off escape routes before they are chosen like if it knows the future.
</Div>
</div>
{{Underline|d8a85c}}
<Div class="lightblock">
== <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em white;border-bottom: 3px groove var(--theme-border-color);">IV. Entrances & Exits</span> ==
{{Underline|d8a85c}}
<Div class="lightblock">
=== <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em white;border-bottom: 3px groove var(--theme-border-color);">IV.I. Entrances</span> ===
* A differently and vividly coloured wall in [[Level 993]] has a rare chance to be a glitching and phase-able wall. [[Phenomenon 1|No-clipping]] through it leads one here.
* Touching a distorted picture of this level within [[Level 918]] teleports the individual to here.
* Climbing up a wacky and awkwardly looping stairs in [[Level 989]] transitions the level to this level.

</div>
<Div class="lightblock">
=== <span style="background:linear-gradient(brown,#FADB6F,brown); -webkit-background-clip:text !important; -webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;text-shadow: 0 0 2em white;border-bottom: 3px groove var(--theme-border-color);">IV.II. Exits</span> ===
* Climbing up a reachable opening, in the [[Level 994|Opened Wackiness]], makes the level become glitchy and unstable. Eventually, teleporting one to [[The Void]].
* Opening an extremely rare door with the label, "Amusement Park," will lead to [[Level 995]].

</div>
</div>
